 :tx/rationale "FIRST-PRINCIPLES ANALYSIS FRAMEWORK — The seven dog-food findings decompose into THREE DEEP THEMES:\n\nTHEME 1: THE CEREMONY-FLOW TENSION (items: harvest noise, skipped observations, session trajectory invisibility)\nAt its core, this is the tension between EXPLICIT KNOWLEDGE CAPTURE (the methodology demands observe → crystallize → task → execute) and IMPLICIT KNOWLEDGE PRODUCTION (the agent produces knowledge continuously as a side-effect of working). The ceremony of explicit capture costs k* tokens and cognitive switching. The radical insight: the methodology should be a FUNCTOR that PRESERVES the agent's natural workflow structure, not a DISTINCT workflow that competes with it.\n\nTHEME 2: THE TITLE-AS-PROMPT PROBLEM (items: task title bloat, schema invisibility)\nEvery task title is a PROMPT that activates the implementer's reasoning. Long titles filled with BACKGROUND/ACCEPTANCE/APPROACH are constraints, not activations. From prompt-optimization: demonstrations > constraints, and the k* threshold means more text often HURTS. The radical insight: the task should be a MULTI-RESOLUTION DOCUMENT with the title as the ACTIVATION SEED (≤25 chars) and the body as the SUPPORTING CONTEXT (available on demand, exactly like ACP).\n\nTHEME 3: THE FOOTER-BODY DUALITY (items: footer/ACP redundancy, guidance-projection gap)\nThe legacy footer and ACP output serve the SAME PURPOSE (tell the agent what to do next) but through DIFFERENT mechanisms (appended text vs structured projection). This duality wastes tokens and creates confusion. The radical insight: the footer IS the output. There should be no distinction between 'the answer' and 'the guidance' — they're the same information projected at different levels. ACP already embodies this insight but the legacy path coexists.\n\nUNIFYING INSIGHT: All three themes are manifestations of ONE underlying problem: BRAID'S OUTPUT IS NOT YET FULLY SELF-SIMILAR. The same information (the action, the context, the methodology state) is represented in different ways at different layers (footer, body, seed, status, task title). Each representation was built independently. ACP started the unification (action-first everywhere). The completion of this unification — where EVERY output surface uses the SAME projection algebra — is the maximally accretive next step."
